import seaborn as sns # enhanced charts

marks = [100,50,70,25]

types of graph in analysis¶

graphs can be 2d or 3d

  • line
  • scatter
  • area
  • bar
  • hist
  • kde
  • boxplot
  • pie
In [23]:
irisdf = sns.load_dataset('iris')

line plot¶

  • use to show ups and downs in s sequence or time series
In [25]:
irisdf['sepal_length'].plot(figsize=(15,5))
Out[25]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a103752310>
In [26]:
irisdf['sepal_length'].plot(figsize=(15,5),style='g--')
plt.show()

scatter plot¶

  • to check the correlation of 2 or 3 series in a dataset
In [27]:
irisdf.plot(kind='scatter',x ='petal_length',y='petal_width')
plt.show()
In [28]:
irisdf.plot(kind='scatter',x ='petal_length',y='petal_width',
            c='petal_length',cmap='cool',marker='^',alpha=.5,
            s=100,title='compairing petals dimensions' , figsize=(10,10))
plt.xticks([])
plt.show()

pie chart¶

  • used for analysing data based on percentage,
  • only takes a single series of data
In [41]:
automobile_df['engine-location'].unique()
Out[41]:
array(['front', 'rear'], dtype=object)
In [42]:
automobile_df['body-style'].unique()
Out[42]:
array(['convertible', 'hatchback', 'sedan', 'wagon', 'hardtop'],
      dtype=object)
In [49]:
automobile_df['engine-location'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie')
Out[49]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a1036e5e20>
In [50]:
automobile_df['body-style'].value_counts()
Out[50]:
sedan          94
hatchback      68
wagon          25
hardtop         8
convertible     6
Name: body-style, dtype: int64
In [54]:
automobile_df['body-style'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie',autopct='%.2f%%')
Out[54]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a10572d4f0>
In [60]:
automobile_df['body-style'].value_counts().plot(
        kind='pie',
        autopct='%.2f%%',
        explode=[0,0,0,0.1,0.1],
        colors = ['#ff9900','#f90909','#f85323','#ffff00','#ff8833','#ff3384'])
Out[60]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a105e46df0>
In [74]:
# donut from pie
automobile_df['body-style'].value_counts().plot(
        kind='pie',
        autopct='%.2f%%',
        wedgeprops={'width':.5},
        pctdistance=.75,
        shadow=True)
plt.show()
In [81]:
automobile_df.corr().plot(kind='kde')
Out[81]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a105cac760>

area plot¶

  • good alternative to line plot. shows ups and downs in a series or set of series
In [88]:
automobile_df['price'].plot(kind='area')
Out[88]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x2a10615f760>
In [90]:
companies = automobile_df['make'].value_counts()
